      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>That's what people always say, that it's just \"subconscious,\" but it feels way more deliberate than that. It’s not just a random feeling. I looked up the logo for VIVID today and it's exactly the same shape as the one in the dream, down to the weird little spark on the corner. And the weirdest part? I haven't seen an ad for them in months, but then I saw a post on my feed today for a different drink that used the exact same shade of neon blue. It feels like they're finding a way to trigger these images in my head. Could there actually be technology that lets companies influence what people dream about? It sounds crazy but it feels so real.",
